      • chain

        public static InstanceFactory chain(InstanceFactory first,
                                    InstanceFactory second,
                                    InstanceFactory... additional)
        Chain two factories together. The second InstanceFactory will only be called if the first returns null, indicating it doesn't support the requested rawType.

        Multiple InstanceFactories can be chained together using this method

        Parameters:
        first - the InstanceFactory that is the start of the chain.
        second - the InstanceFactory that should be called if the first returns null.
        additional - additional InstanceFactory that can be called if previous factories return null
        Returns:
        a InstanceFactory that encapsulates the chained factories.
